Description: An identifier for the set of data. May be a global unique identifier or an identifier specific to a collection or institution.
Examples: The ScienceBase ID number of the dataset

Description: The nature or genre of the resource.
Examples: This will be "Water Quality and Physical Habitat Structure" for all values in this data set.

Description: The name identifying the data set from which the record was derived.
A bibliographic reference for the resource as a statement indicating how this record should be cited (attributed) when used.
The most recent date-time on which the datasets were combind.
Examples: Recommended best practice is to use a date that conforms to ISO 8601:2004(E).

Description: The name (or acronym) in use by the institution having custody of the object(s) or information referred to in the record
Examples: For this implementation of the Darwin Core, this represents the institution who oversees the orgian data sets. Examples:  BLM AIM, EPA NRSA , USFS AREMP, USFS PIBO

Description: Integer identifier referencing the record in the ISOMetadata table for this source.
